Warnino  () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Biesiekierz, within Koszalin County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  west of Biesiekierz,  south-west of Koszalin, and  north-east of the regional capital Szczecin.
For the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
